The paper discusses a specific issue with batch normalization in deep learning models and proposes a solution to address it. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves statistical analysis and proposes a new method for estimating normalization statistics, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments involve object detection, which could also fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing and understanding visual data.
